snippet: Egyptians appear to be barely lifting a finger as the Gaza death toll mounts, leaving the Palestinians and the Israelis without a go-between.
abstract: Egypt appears willing to sit out latest crisis between Israel and Palestinians, even though it has acted as mediator between the two again and again over decades; position reflects shifts in Egypt's foreign policy under Pres Abdel-Fattah el-Sisi.
lead_paragraph: Egyptians appear to be barely lifting a finger as the Gaza death toll mounts, leaving the Palestinians and the Israelis without a go-between.

headline.main: Egypt Silent as Neighbors Wage Battles
headline.print_headline: Egypt Silent as Neighbors Wage Battles
